Quick check: N/A (no changes).

Analysis summary (4+ sessions):
  CocycleFactorsThroughELevel states: β(x,u,v) = fE(τ(x,v).fst) - fE(τ(x,u).fst)
  for some fE : E'N → ℤ. Equivalent to: β is a coboundary at the finite E-level.

  Approaches explored:
  1. ScottIntCodomain on E directly: needs global section t : (x:S) → T(x), unavailable.
  2. FC.choice at finite level: gets section σ but can't lift back to evaluate β.
  3. ScottIntCodomain on E×E (StoneProduct): factors β̃ through (E×E)-level,
     but relating (E×E)-level to E-level requires "generation fact" (~150+ lines).
  4. localChoice + closedFamilyChoice: gets section of q, defines α(x,u)=β(x,w(c),u).
     α depends on choice of c, not well-defined. d₀(α) IS well-defined = β, but need actual α.
  5. Fiber product FP = Σ S (λ x → T x × T x): Stone via StoneSigmaClosed+StoneProduct.
     ScottIntCodomain on FP factors β̃. But FP-level and E-level are unrelated.
  6. DecompData (lemDecompColimMorphisms): relates FP-level → E-level. Need generation
     fact: FP ring generated by E-ring pullbacks along two projections.
  7. Colimit approach (tex proof): Č(S,T,ℤ) = colim Č(S_k,T_k,ℤ), each exact.
     Equivalent to the postulate. Requires compatible ring decomposition infrastructure.
  8. FC.choice section + section-exact at finite level: works when π injective on fibers.
     Fails when multiple S-elements collapse (need higher level, i.e., generation fact).

  Fundamental blocker: ALL approaches require relating the ring decomposition of FP
  (or E×E, or E×_S E) to the ring decomposition of E. This "generation fact" —
  that B-FP is generated by pullbacks from B-E — is true but requires ~150-200 lines
  of new infrastructure tracing through StoneSigmaClosed/StoneProduct constructions.

